            <h2 class="text-justify">Bar Harbor</h2>
            <p class="text-justify">Bar Harbor has a century-long reputation for being a scenic town that combines all the state's best qualities. Bar Harbor is also known as the gateway to Acadia National Park. The town is located along with Frenchman. Hence the travellers get a soothing view both left and right. The craggy coastline looks like a landscape painting, making tourists love the beauty. </p>

